# Testing rules

## Backend (Python + pytest)
- Test runner: pytest
- Test location: backend/tests/
- Test file naming: test_<module_name>.py (e.g. test_build_tree.py)
- Fixtures: use backend/tests/fixtures/sample_project/ as a fake ~/projects
  This folder must contain:
  - At least 2 subfolders
  - At least 3 files total
  - One subfolder that is a git repo with at least one unstaged change
  - One subfolder that is a clean git repo (no changes)
- Assertions:
  - Always assert the full node schema shape, not just one field
  - Use assert isinstance(node["id"], str) style checks

## Frontend (Vitest)
- Test runner: Vitest (not Jest)
- Test location: frontend/src/__tests__/
- Test file naming: <module>.test.js (e.g. buildRingLayout.test.js)
- Do not test Three.js rendering directly — test utility functions only
  (buildRingLayout, loadTree, traverseTree)
- Use vi.mock() for fetch calls in loadTree tests

## Universal rules
- Every new function must have at least one test before the task is marked done
- Never delete a test unless it is demonstrably wrong and you explain why
- Never mark a task done if any test is failing
- If a test is flaky (passes sometimes), fix the cause — do not skip the test
- Run tests before writing the handoff note

## Run commands
- Backend: cd backend && python -m pytest tests/ -v
- Frontend: cd frontend && npm test